                <h1>Key Facts About Thurgood Marshall</h1>
                <p>Thurgood Marshall was the first African American Supreme Court Justice, serving from 1967 to 1991. He was instrumental in the landmark case Brown v. Board of Education, which desegregated public schools. Marshall dedicated his career to civil rights, advocating for social justice and equal rights under the law.</p>
